cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper discusses the design and optimization of a replicated data type, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Specifically, the paper focuses on sets, which are a common data structure in computer science and fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses conflict-free replicated data types, which are a subfield of distributed databases (cs.DB). The proposed optimization to avoid tombstones involves a trade-off between space and time complexity, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the consistency semantics of the replicated set, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
